FIFA on Thursday announced the final three nominees for the Best FIFA Men’s Coach and The Best FIFA Women’s Coach for 2021. The winner will be chosen by an international jury comprising a panel of FIFA Legends and registered fans across the world on FIFA’s official website. Recall that FIFA had on Wednesday announced the final three nominees for Men’s and Women’s Best goalkeeper for 2021. The virtual awards ceremony will take place in Zurich on January 17 and it will be broadcast live from the home of FIFA. The final three nominees for The Best FIFA Women’s Coach are (in alphabetical order): Lluís Cortés (Spain / FC Barcelona) Emma Hayes (England / Chelsea FC Women) Sarina Wiegman (Netherlands / Dutch national team / English national team) The final three nominees for The Best FIFA Men’s Coach are (in alphabetical order): Pep Guardiola (Spain / Manchester City FC) Roberto Mancini (Italy / Italian national team) Thomas Tuchel (Germany / Chelsea FC)